This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it presents a dataset of annotated Wikipedia texts across multiple languages, which can be used for various NLP tasks such as named entity recognition, entity linking, and text classification. 

It is also likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as the dataset includes mention entity co-occurrence counts and can be used for information retrieval tasks such as query expansion and document ranking. 

The paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it presents entity embeddings derived from the dataset, which can be used for various machine learning tasks such as clustering and classification. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the dataset can be used for various AI tasks such as knowledge representation and reasoning. 

Finally, the Database (cs.DB) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper discusses the methodology used to generate the dataset, which involves enriching Wikipedia markup to increase the number of links, and the dataset includes mappings between Freebase ids and Wikidata item ids.
